fundamentals.description:
This clause specifies the requirements for the exchange of multidisciplinary analysis and design information. The management of the configuration of products is addressed in this application protocol, and is concerned with authorizations and the associated approvals given by persons in organizations. The structured list of materials or components needed to make a product can be exchanged, along with initial part design requirements as well as requirements for revised part versions. It provides the directive for work to proceed on these initial or modified part versions.
This part provides information about the planned usage of components in a product model, and also includes data about the different products that are sold by an organization to its customers enabling an organization to control the configuration of these products. It contains the structure through which a part, unique versions of a part, and different design and analysis discipline views of a part can be defined.
In addition this part provides a generic engineering analysis framework as a basis for sharing classical finite element, computational fluid dynamic, and generic mesh based numerical analyses, each of which may have discrete or continuous field defined properties. These analyses and their properties are fully associative to the part shape and product information.
The details of these views and other relevant information are organized in conformance options. An overview of the available conformance options is given here.
The Classical finite element analysis conformance options are:
Finite elements;
FEA material aspect;
Finite element shape;
Finite element analysis.
The Computational fluid dynamics conformance options are:
Cfd model;
Cfd specified general property;
Cfd conditions;
Cfd equations;
Cfd results.
The Field defined properties for classical finite element analysis conformance options are:
Fea_definition_relationships.
The Generic engineering analysis framework conformance options are:
Analysis;
Anlysis product relationships;
Product analysis.
The Generic mesh based numerical analysis conformance options are:
Mesh connectivity;
Mesh topology;
Mesh functions.
